KAZEEM AWOJOODU, PATIENCE OGBODO IBADAN/ENUGU Oyo State Commissioner of Police, Ngozi Onadeko, has assured residents across the state of maximum security, before, during and after the Eid-il-Fitri celebrations. Onadeko, in a statement issued by the state Police Public Relations Officer SP. Adewale Osifeso, stated that comprehensive security had been put in place to ensure crime free Eid-il-Fitri celebrations across the state. Similarly, the Commissioner of Police, Enugu State Command, Abubakar Lawal, reiterated his command’s commitment to collaborate with other security agencies and stakeholders to provide adequate security during and beyond the periods of the commemoration Workers’ Day and Eid-el-Fitr celebration. The CP, in a statement made available to journalists in Enugu on Saturday ordered Area Commanders, Divisional Police Officers and Heads of Tactical/Operational Units of the command to ensure the maximum deployment of the human, operational and intelligence assets at their disposal, to visibly patrol and police identified flashpoints, streets and other places of public interest.